#. <section class="sutta" id="an3.60"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an3.60:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 3"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 3"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an3.60:0.2"
msgid "6. Brāhmaṇavagga"
msgstr "6. Brahmins"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an3.60:0.3"
msgid "60. Saṅgāravasutta"
msgstr "60. With Saṅgārava"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā "
"bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi."
msgstr ""
"Then Saṅgārava the brahmin went up to the Buddha, and exchanged greetings "
"with him."

msgctxt "an3.60:1.2"
msgid ""
"Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ "
"nisinno kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"When the greetings and polite conversation were over, he sat down to one "
"side and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an3.60:1.3"
msgid "“mayamassu, bho gotama, brāhmaṇā nāma."
msgstr "“Master Gotama, we who are called brahmins"

msgctxt "an3.60:1.4"
msgid "Yaññaṃ yajāmapi yajāpemapi."
msgstr "make sacrifices and encourage others to make sacrifices."

#. VAR: gotama, yo ceva yajati → yo ceva yaññaṃ yajati (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: puññappaṭipadaṃ → puññapaṭipadaṃ (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.60:1.5"
msgid ""
"Tatra, bho gotama, yo ceva yajati yo ca yajāpeti sabbe te anekasārīrikaṃ "
"puññappaṭipadaṃ paṭipannā honti, yadidaṃ yaññādhikaraṇaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now, Master Gotama, both of these people—the one who sacrifices and the one "
"who encourages others to sacrifice—are doing good for many people on account "
"of that sacrifice."

msgctxt "an3.60:1.6"
msgid ""
"Yo panāyaṃ, bho gotama, yassa vā tassa vā kulā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito "
"ekamattānaṃ dameti, ekamattānaṃ sameti, ekamattānaṃ parinibbāpeti, "
"evamassāyaṃ ekasārīrikaṃ puññappaṭipadaṃ paṭipanno hoti, yadidaṃ "
"pabbajjādhikaraṇan”ti."
msgstr ""
"But, Master Gotama, when someone has gone forth from the lay life to "
"homelessness, they tame, calm, and extinguish themselves alone. That being "
"so, they are doing good for just one person on account of that going forth.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.169"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Tena hi, brāhmaṇa, taññevettha paṭipucchissāmi. Yathā te khameyya tathā naṃ "
"byākareyyāsi."
msgstr ""
"“Well then, brahmin, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer "
"as you like."

msgctxt "an3.60:2.2"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa, "
msgstr "What do you think, brahmin? "

msgctxt "an3.60:2.3"
msgid ""
"idha tathāgato loke uppajjati arahaṃ sammāsambuddho vijjācaraṇasampanno "
"sugato lokavidū anuttaro purisadammasārathi satthā devamanussānaṃ buddho "
"bhagavā."
msgstr ""
"A Realized One arises in the world, perfected, a fully awakened Buddha, "
"accomplished in knowledge and conduct, holy, knower of the world, supreme "
"guide for those who wish to train, teacher of gods and humans, awakened, "
"blessed."

msgctxt "an3.60:2.4"
msgid "So evamāha:"
msgstr "He says,"

msgctxt "an3.60:2.5"
msgid ""
"‘ethāyaṃ maggo ayaṃ paṭipadā yathāpaṭipanno ahaṃ anuttaraṃ "
"brahmacariyogadhaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā pavedemi;"
msgstr ""
"‘Come, this is the path, this is the practice. Practicing like this, I "
"realized the supreme culmination of the spiritual life with my own insight, "
"and I make it known."

#. VAR: etha → etaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "an3.60:2.6"
msgid ""
"etha, tumhepi tathā paṭipajjatha, yathāpaṭipannā tumhepi anuttaraṃ "
"brahmacariyogadhaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti."
msgstr ""
"Please, all of you, practice like this, and you too will realize the supreme "
"culmination of the spiritual life, and will live having realized it with "
"your own insight.’"

#. VAR: ayañceva → sayaṃ ceva (mr)
msgctxt "an3.60:2.7"
msgid ""
"Iti ayañceva satthā dhammaṃ deseti, pare ca tathatthāya paṭipajjanti, tāni "
"kho pana honti anekānipi satāni anekānipi sahassāni anekānipi satasahassāni."
msgstr ""
"So the teacher teaches Dhamma, and others practice accordingly, in their "
"hundreds and thousands, and hundreds of thousands."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, brāhmaṇa, "
msgstr "What do you think, brahmin? "

msgctxt "an3.60:3.2"
msgid ""
"iccāyaṃ evaṃ sante ekasārīrikā vā puññappaṭipadā hoti anekasārīrikā vā, "
"yadidaṃ pabbajjādhikaraṇan”ti?"
msgstr ""
"This being so, are they doing good for just one person or for many people on "
"account of going forth?”"

#. VAR: Iccāyampi → iccāyante (mr)
msgctxt "an3.60:3.3"
msgid ""
"“Iccāyampi, bho gotama, evaṃ sante anekasārīrikā puññappaṭipadā hoti, "
"yadidaṃ pabbajjādhikaraṇan”ti."
msgstr ""
"“This being so, Master Gotama, they are doing good for many people on "
"account of going forth.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, āyasmā ānando saṅgāravaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "When he said this, Venerable Ānanda said to Saṅgārava:"

msgctxt "an3.60:4.2"
msgid ""
"“imāsaṃ te, brāhmaṇa, dvinnaṃ paṭipadānaṃ katamā paṭipadā khamati "
"appatthatarā ca appasamārambhatarā ca mahapphalatarā ca mahānisaṃsatarā "
"cā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Brahmin, which of these two practices do you believe has fewer requirements "
"and undertakings, yet is more fruitful and beneficial?”"

msgctxt "an3.60:4.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Saṅgārava said to Ānanda:"

msgctxt "an3.60:4.4"
msgid "“seyyathāpi bhavaṃ gotamo bhavaṃ cānando."
msgstr "“Those such as Masters Gotama and Ānanda"

msgctxt "an3.60:4.5"
msgid "Ete me pujjā, ete me pāsaṃsā”ti."
msgstr "are honored and praised by me!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:5.1"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho āyasmā ānando saṅgāravaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time, Ānanda said to Saṅgārava:"

msgctxt "an3.60:5.2"
msgid "“na kho tyāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, evaṃ pucchāmi:"
msgstr "“Brahmin, I didn’t ask you"

msgctxt "an3.60:5.3"
msgid "‘ke vā te pujjā ke vā te pāsaṃsā’ti?"
msgstr "who you honor and praise."

msgctxt "an3.60:5.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho tyāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, pucchāmi:"
msgstr "I asked you,"

msgctxt "an3.60:5.5"
msgid ""
"‘imāsaṃ te, brāhmaṇa, dvinnaṃ paṭipadānaṃ katamā paṭipadā khamati "
"appatthatarā ca appasamārambhatarā ca mahapphalatarā ca mahānisaṃsatarā "
"cā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"which of these two practices do you believe has fewer requirements and "
"undertakings, yet is more fruitful and beneficial?”"

msgctxt "an3.60:5.6"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a second time Saṅgārava said to Ānanda:"

msgctxt "an3.60:5.7"
msgid "“seyyathāpi bhavaṃ gotamo bhavaṃ cānando."
msgstr "“Those such as Masters Gotama and Ānanda"

msgctxt "an3.60:5.8"
msgid "Ete me pujjā, ete me pāsaṃsā”ti."
msgstr "are honored and praised by me!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:6.1"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho āyasmā ānando saṅgāravaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a third time, Ānanda said to Saṅgārava:"

msgctxt "an3.60:6.2"
msgid "“na kho tyāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, evaṃ pucchāmi:"
msgstr "“Brahmin, I didn’t ask you"

msgctxt "an3.60:6.3"
msgid "‘ke vā te pujjā ke vā te pāsaṃsā’ti?"
msgstr "who you honor and praise."

msgctxt "an3.60:6.4"
msgid "Evaṃ kho tyāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, pucchāmi:"
msgstr "I asked you,"

msgctxt "an3.60:6.5"
msgid ""
"‘imāsaṃ te, brāhmaṇa, dvinnaṃ paṭipadānaṃ katamā paṭipadā khamati "
"appatthatarā ca appasamārambhatarā ca mahapphalatarā ca mahānisaṃsatarā "
"cā’”ti?"
msgstr ""
"which of these two practices do you believe has fewer requirements and "
"undertakings, yet is more fruitful and beneficial?”"

msgctxt "an3.60:6.6"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "For a third time Saṅgārava said to Ānanda:"

msgctxt "an3.60:6.7"
msgid "“seyyathāpi bhavaṃ gotamo bhavaṃ cānando."
msgstr "“Those such as Masters Gotama and Ānanda"

msgctxt "an3.60:6.8"
msgid "Ete me pujjā, ete me pāsaṃsā”ti."
msgstr "are honored and praised by me!”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.170"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato etadahosi:"
msgstr "Then it occurred to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an3.60:7.2"
msgid ""
"“yāva tatiyampi kho saṅgāravo brāhmaṇo ānandena sahadhammikaṃ pañhaṃ puṭṭho "
"saṃsādeti no vissajjeti."
msgstr ""
"“Though Ānanda asked him a sensible question three times, Saṅgārava falters "
"without answering."

msgctxt "an3.60:7.3"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ parimoceyyan”ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I give him a way out?”"

msgctxt "an3.60:7.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā saṅgāravaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then the Buddha said to Saṅgārava:"

# reading rajaparisayam, in line with sn 42.10
#. VAR: nvajja → kānujja (bj, pts1)
#. VAR: rājapurisānaṃ → rājaparisāyaṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.60:7.5"
msgid ""
"“kā nvajja, brāhmaṇa, rājantepure rājapurisānaṃ sannisinnānaṃ sannipatitānaṃ "
"antarākathā udapādī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“Brahmin, what came up in the conversation among the king’s retinue today, "
"sitting together in the royal compound?”"

msgctxt "an3.60:7.6"
msgid ""
"“Ayaṃ khvajja, bho gotama, rājantepure rājapurisānaṃ sannisinnānaṃ "
"sannipatitānaṃ antarākathā udapādi:"
msgstr "“Master Gotama, this came up:"

msgctxt "an3.60:7.7"
msgid ""
"‘pubbe sudaṃ appatarā ceva bhikkhū ahesuṃ bahutarā ca uttari manussadhammā "
"iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ dassesuṃ;"
msgstr ""
"‘Formerly, it seems, there were fewer mendicants, but more of them displayed "
"superhuman demonstrations of psychic power;"

msgctxt "an3.60:7.8"
msgid ""
"etarahi pana bahutarā ceva bhikkhū appatarā ca uttari manussadhammā "
"iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ dassentī’ti."
msgstr ""
"while these days, there are more mendicants, but fewer display superhuman "
"demonstrations of psychic power.’"

msgctxt "an3.60:7.9"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ khvajja, bho gotama, rājantepure rājapurisānaṃ sannisinnānaṃ "
"sannipatitānaṃ antarākathā udapādī”ti."
msgstr ""
"This is what came up in the conversation among the king’s retinue today, "
"while sitting together in the royal compound.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:8.1"
msgid "“Tīṇi kho imāni, brāhmaṇa, pāṭihāriyāni."
msgstr "“Brahmin, there are three kinds of demonstration."

msgctxt "an3.60:8.2"
msgid "Katamāni tīṇi?"
msgstr "What three?"

msgctxt "an3.60:8.3"
msgid "Iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ, ādesanāpāṭihāriyaṃ, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ."
msgstr ""
"A demonstration of psychic power, a demonstration of revealing, and an "
"instructional demonstration."

msgctxt "an3.60:8.4"
msgid "Katamañca, brāhmaṇa, iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the demonstration of psychic power?"

#. VAR: abhijjamāne → abhejjamāne (bj) | abhijjamāno (pts1)
msgctxt "an3.60:8.5"
msgid ""
"Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti: ‘ekopi hutvā "
"bahudhā hoti, bahudhāpi hutvā eko hoti; āvibhāvaṃ, tirobhāvaṃ; tirokuṭṭaṃ "
"tiropākāraṃ tiropabbataṃ asajjamāno gacchati, seyyathāpi ākāse; pathaviyāpi "
"ummujjanimujjaṃ karoti, seyyathāpi udake; udakepi abhijjamāne gacchati, "
"seyyathāpi pathaviyaṃ; ākāsepi pallaṅkena kamati, seyyathāpi pakkhī sakuṇo; "
"imepi candimasūriye evaṃmahiddhike evaṃmahānubhāve pāṇinā parimasati "
"parimajjati, yāva brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti’."
msgstr ""
"It’s when someone wields the many kinds of psychic power: multiplying "
"themselves and becoming one again; appearing and disappearing; going "
"unimpeded through a wall, a rampart, or a mountain as if through space; "
"diving in and out of the earth as if it were water; walking on water as if "
"it were earth; flying cross-legged through the sky like a bird; touching and "
"stroking with the hand the sun and moon, so mighty and powerful. They "
"control the body as far as the Brahmā realm."

msgctxt "an3.60:8.6"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, iddhipāṭihāriyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the demonstration of psychic power."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:9.1"
msgid "Katamañca, brāhmaṇa, ādesanāpāṭihāriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is the demonstration of revealing?"

msgctxt "an3.60:9.2"
msgid "Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco nimittena ādisati:"
msgstr "In one case, someone reveals by means of a sign:"

msgctxt "an3.60:9.3"
msgid "‘evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is what you’re thinking, such is your thought, and thus is your state "
"of mind.’"

msgctxt "an3.60:9.4"
msgid "So bahuñcepi ādisati tatheva taṃ hoti, no aññathā."
msgstr ""
"And even if they reveal this many times, it turns out exactly so, not "
"otherwise."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.171"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc10"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:10.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco na heva kho nimittena ādisati, api ca kho "
"manussānaṃ vā amanussānaṃ vā devatānaṃ vā saddaṃ sutvā ādisati:"
msgstr ""
"In another case, someone reveals after hearing it from humans or non-humans "
"or deities:"

msgctxt "an3.60:10.2"
msgid "‘evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is what you’re thinking, such is your thought, and thus is your state "
"of mind.’"

msgctxt "an3.60:10.3"
msgid "So bahuñcepi ādisati tatheva taṃ hoti, no aññathā."
msgstr ""
"And even if they reveal this many times, it turns out exactly so, not "
"otherwise."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc11"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:11.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco na heva kho nimittena ādisati napi manussānaṃ vā "
"amanussānaṃ vā devatānaṃ vā saddaṃ sutvā ādisati, api ca kho vitakkayato "
"vicārayato vitakkavipphārasaddaṃ sutvā ādisati:"
msgstr ""
"In another case, someone reveals by hearing the sound of thought spreading "
"as someone thinks and considers:"

msgctxt "an3.60:11.2"
msgid "‘evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘This is what you’re thinking, such is your thought, and thus is your state "
"of mind.’"

msgctxt "an3.60:11.3"
msgid "So bahuñcepi ādisati tatheva taṃ hoti, no aññathā."
msgstr ""
"And even if they reveal this many times, it turns out exactly so, not "
"otherwise."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc12"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:12.1"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, brāhmaṇa, ekacco na heva kho nimittena ādisati, napi manussānaṃ "
"vā amanussānaṃ vā devatānaṃ vā saddaṃ sutvā ādisati, napi vitakkayato "
"vicārayato vitakkavipphārasaddaṃ sutvā ādisati, api ca kho avitakkaṃ "
"avicāraṃ samādhiṃ samāpannassa cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti:"
msgstr ""
"In another case, someone comprehends the mind of a person who has attained "
"the immersion that’s free of placing the mind and keeping it connected. They "
"understand:"

msgctxt "an3.60:12.2"
msgid ""
"‘yathā imassa bhoto manosaṅkhārā paṇihitā imassa cittassa anantarā amuṃ nāma "
"vitakkaṃ vitakkessatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Judging by the way this person’s intentions are directed, immediately after "
"this mind state, they’ll think this thought.’"

msgctxt "an3.60:12.3"
msgid "So bahuñcepi ādisati tatheva taṃ hoti, no aññathā."
msgstr ""
"And even if they reveal this many times, it turns out exactly so, not "
"otherwise."

msgctxt "an3.60:12.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, ādesanāpāṭihāriyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called the demonstration of revealing."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc13"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:13.1"
msgid "Katamañca, brāhmaṇa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ?"
msgstr "And what is an instructional demonstration?"

msgctxt "an3.60:13.2"
msgid "Idha, brāhmaṇa, ekacco evamanusāsati:"
msgstr "It’s when someone instructs others like this:"

msgctxt "an3.60:13.3"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃ vitakketha, mā evaṃ vitakkayittha; evaṃ manasi karotha, mā evaṃ "
"manasākattha; idaṃ pajahatha, idaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Think like this, not like that. Focus your mind like this, not like that. "
"Give up this, and live having achieved that.’"

msgctxt "an3.60:13.4"
msgid "Idaṃ vuccati, brāhmaṇa, anusāsanīpāṭihāriyaṃ."
msgstr "This is called an instructional demonstration."

msgctxt "an3.60:13.5"
msgid "Imāni kho, brāhmaṇa, tīṇi pāṭihāriyāni."
msgstr "These are the three kinds of demonstration."

msgctxt "an3.60:13.6"
msgid ""
"Imesaṃ te, brāhmaṇa, tiṇṇaṃ pāṭihāriyānaṃ katamaṃ pāṭihāriyaṃ khamati "
"abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañcā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"Of these three kinds of demonstration, which do you consider to be the "
"finest?”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc14"></a>
#. VAR: yadidaṃ → yamidaṃ (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.60:14.1"
msgid ""
"“Tatra, bho gotama, yadidaṃ pāṭihāriyaṃ idhekacco anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ "
"paccanubhoti … pe …"
msgstr "“Regarding this, Master Gotama, a demonstration of psychic power"

#. VAR: yova → yo ca (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: sova → so ca (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: yova → yo ca (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: tasseva → tassa ceva (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.60:14.2"
msgid "yāva brāhmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti,"
msgstr ""

#. VAR: yova → yo ca (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: sova → so ca (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: yova → yo ca (s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
#. VAR: tasseva → tassa ceva (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "an3.60:14.3"
msgid ""
"idaṃ, bho gotama, pāṭihāriyaṃ yova naṃ karoti sova naṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, yova "
"naṃ karoti tasseva taṃ hoti."
msgstr "is experienced only by the one who performs it, occurring only to them."

msgctxt "an3.60:14.4"
msgid "Idaṃ me, bho gotama, pāṭihāriyaṃ māyāsahadhammarūpaṃ viya khāyati."
msgstr "This seems to me like a magic trick."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.172"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc15"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:15.1"
msgid "Yampidaṃ, bho gotama, pāṭihāriyaṃ idhekacco nimittena ādisati:"
msgstr ""
"And the demonstration where someone reveals something by means of a sign,"

msgctxt "an3.60:15.2"
msgid ""
"‘evampi te mano, itthampi te mano, itipi te cittan’ti, so bahuñcepi ādisati "
"tatheva taṃ hoti, no aññathā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.60:15.3"
msgid ""
"Idha pana, bho gotama, ekacco na heva kho nimittena ādisati, api ca kho "
"manussānaṃ vā amanussānaṃ vā devatānaṃ vā saddaṃ sutvā ādisati … pe …"
msgstr "or after hearing it from human, non-humans, or deities,"

msgctxt "an3.60:15.4"
msgid ""
"napi manussānaṃ vā amanussānaṃ vā devatānaṃ vā saddaṃ sutvā ādisati, api ca "
"kho vitakkayato vicārayato vitakkavipphārasaddaṃ sutvā ādisati … pe …"
msgstr ""
"or by hearing the sound of thought spreading as someone thinks and considers,"

msgctxt "an3.60:15.5"
msgid ""
"napi vitakkayato vicārayato vitakkavipphārasaddaṃ sutvā ādisati, api ca kho "
"avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhiṃ samāpannassa cetasā ceto paricca pajānāti:"
msgstr "or by comprehending the mind of another person,"

msgctxt "an3.60:15.6"
msgid ""
"‘yathā imassa bhoto manosaṅkhārā paṇihitā imassa cittassa anantarā amhaṃ "
"nāma vitakkaṃ vitakkessatī’ti, so bahuñcepi ādisati tatheva taṃ hoti, no "
"aññathā."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "an3.60:15.7"
msgid ""
"Idampi, bho gotama, pāṭihāriyaṃ yova naṃ karoti sova naṃ paṭisaṃvedeti, yova "
"naṃ karoti tasseva taṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"is also experienced only by the one who performs it, occurring only to them."

msgctxt "an3.60:15.8"
msgid "Idampi me, bho gotama, pāṭihāriyaṃ māyāsahadhammarūpaṃ viya khāyati."
msgstr "This also seems to me like a magic trick."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc16"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:16.1"
msgid "Yañca kho idaṃ, bho gotama, pāṭihāriyaṃ idhekacco evaṃ anusāsati:"
msgstr "But as to the demonstration where someone instructs others:"

msgctxt "an3.60:16.2"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃ vitakketha, mā evaṃ vitakkayittha; evaṃ manasi karotha, mā evaṃ "
"manasākattha; idaṃ pajahatha, idaṃ upasampajja viharathā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Think like this, not like that. Focus your mind like this, not like that. "
"Give up this, and live having achieved that.’"

msgctxt "an3.60:16.3"
msgid ""
"Idameva, bho gotama, pāṭihāriyaṃ khamati imesaṃ tiṇṇaṃ pāṭihāriyānaṃ "
"abhikkantatarañca paṇītatarañca."
msgstr ""
"I prefer this demonstration, Master Gotama. It’s the finest of the three "
"kinds of demonstration."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc17"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:17.1"
msgid "Acchariyaṃ, bho gotama, abbhutaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "It’s incredible, Master Gotama, it’s amazing,"

msgctxt "an3.60:17.2"
msgid ""
"Yāvasubhāsitamidaṃ bhotā gotamena imehi ca mayaṃ tīhi pāṭihāriyehi "
"samannāgataṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ dhārema."
msgstr ""
"how well said this was said by Master Gotama. We regard Master Gotama as "
"someone who possesses these three kinds of demonstration."

msgctxt "an3.60:17.3"
msgid ""
"Bhavañhi gotamo anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhoti … pe … yāva "
"brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vatteti, "
msgstr ""
"For Master Gotama wields the many kinds of psychic power … controlling the "
"body as far as the Brahmā realm. "

msgctxt "an3.60:17.4"
msgid ""
"bhavañhi gotamo avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhiṃ samāpannassa cetasā ceto paricca "
"pajānāti:"
msgstr ""
"And Master Gotama comprehends the mind of another person who has attained "
"the immersion that is free of placing the mind and keeping it connected. He "
"understands:"

msgctxt "an3.60:17.5"
msgid ""
"‘yathā imassa bhoto manosaṅkhārā paṇihitā imassa cittassa anantarā amuṃ nāma "
"vitakkaṃ vitakkessatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Judging by the way this person’s intentions are directed, immediately after "
"this mind state they’ll think this thought.’"

msgctxt "an3.60:17.6"
msgid "Bhavañhi gotamo evamanusāsati:"
msgstr "And Master Gotama instructs others like this:"

msgctxt "an3.60:17.7"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃ vitakketha, mā evaṃ vitakkayittha; evaṃ manasi karotha, mā evaṃ "
"manasākattha; idaṃ pajahatha, idaṃ upasampajja viharathā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Think like this, not like that. Focus your mind like this, not like that. "
"Give up this, and live having achieved that.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc18"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:18.1"
msgid "“Addhā kho tyāhaṃ, brāhmaṇa, āsajja upanīya vācā bhāsitā;"
msgstr "“Your words are clearly invasive and intrusive, brahmin."

msgctxt "an3.60:18.2"
msgid "api ca tyāhaṃ byākarissāmi."
msgstr "Nevertheless, I will answer you."

msgctxt "an3.60:18.3"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, brāhmaṇa, anekavihitaṃ iddhividhaṃ paccanubhomi … pe … yāva "
"brahmalokāpi kāyena vasaṃ vattemi."
msgstr ""
"For I do wield the many kinds of psychic power … controlling the body as far "
"as the Brahmā realm."

msgctxt "an3.60:18.4"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, brāhmaṇa, avitakkaṃ avicāraṃ samādhiṃ samāpannassa cetasā ceto "
"paricca pajānāmi:"
msgstr ""
"And I do comprehend the mind of another person who has attained the "
"immersion that is free of placing the mind and keeping it connected. I "
"understand:"

msgctxt "an3.60:18.5"
msgid ""
"‘yathā imassa bhoto manosaṅkhārā paṇihitā, imassa cittassa anantarā amuṃ "
"nāma vitakkaṃ vitakkessatī’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Judging by the way this person’s intentions are directed, immediately after "
"this mind state they’ll think this thought.’"

msgctxt "an3.60:18.6"
msgid "Ahañhi, brāhmaṇa, evamanusāsāmi:"
msgstr "And I do instruct others like this:"

msgctxt "an3.60:18.7"
msgid ""
"‘evaṃ vitakketha, mā evaṃ vitakkayittha; evaṃ manasi karotha, mā evaṃ "
"manasākattha; idaṃ pajahatha, idaṃ upasampajja viharathā’”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Think like this, not like that. Focus your mind like this, not like that. "
"Give up this, and live having achieved that.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli1.173"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc19"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:19.1"
msgid ""
"“Atthi pana, bho gotama, añño ekabhikkhupi yo imehi tīhi pāṭihāriyehi "
"samannāgato, aññatra bhotā gotamenā”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But Master Gotama, is there even one other mendicant who possesses these "
"three kinds of demonstration, apart from Master Gotama?”"

#. VAR: ye → te (mr)
msgctxt "an3.60:19.2"
msgid ""
"“Na kho, brāhmaṇa, ekaṃyeva sataṃ na dve satāni na tīṇi satāni na cattāri "
"satāni na pañca satāni, atha kho bhiyyova, ye bhikkhū imehi tīhi "
"pāṭihāriyehi samannāgatā”ti."
msgstr ""
"“There’s not just one hundred mendicants, brahmin, who possess these three "
"kinds of demonstration, nor two, three, four, or five hundred, but many more "
"than that.”"

msgctxt "an3.60:19.3"
msgid "“Kahaṃ pana, bho gotama, etarahi te bhikkhū viharantī”ti?"
msgstr "“But where are these mendicants now staying?”"

msgctxt "an3.60:19.4"
msgid "“Imasmiṃyeva kho, brāhmaṇa, bhikkhusaṃghe”ti."
msgstr "“Right here, brahmin, in this Saṅgha of mendicants.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc20"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:20.1"
msgid "“Abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama, abhikkantaṃ, bho gotama."
msgstr "“Excellent, Master Gotama! Excellent!"

msgctxt "an3.60:20.2"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bho gotama, nikkujjitaṃ vā ukkujjeyya, paṭicchannaṃ vā "
"vivareyya, mūḷhassa vā maggaṃ ācikkheyya, andhakāre vā telapajjotaṃ dhāreyya:"
" ‘cakkhumanto rūpāni dakkhantī’ti; evamevaṃ bhotā gotamena anekapariyāyena "
"dhammo pakāsito."
msgstr ""
"As if he were righting the overturned, or revealing the hidden, or pointing "
"out the path to the lost, or lighting a lamp in the dark so people with good "
"eyes can see what’s there, Master Gotama has made the teaching clear in many "
"ways."

msgctxt "an3.60:20.3"
msgid "Esāhaṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ saraṇaṃ gacchāmi, dhammañca bhikkhusaṅghañca."
msgstr ""
"I go for refuge to Master Gotama, to the teaching, and to the mendicant "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "an3.60:20.4"
msgid ""
"Upāsakaṃ maṃ bhavaṃ gotamo dhāretu ajjatagge pāṇupetaṃ saraṇaṃ gatan”ti."
msgstr ""
"From this day forth, may Master Gotama remember me as a lay follower who has "
"gone for refuge for life.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.60:20.5"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an3.60:20.6"
msgid "Brāhmaṇavaggo paṭhamo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc21"></a>
msgctxt "an3.60:21.1"
msgid "Dve brāhmaṇā caññataro,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.60:21.2"
msgid "paribbājakena nibbutaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.60:21.3"
msgid "Palokavaccho tikaṇṇo,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "an3.60:21.4"
msgid "soṇi saṅgāravena cāti."
msgstr ""
